p: The total monounsaturated fatty acid (MUFA) content followed a similar trend as it progressively augmented with increasing the dietary BSF inclusion level (35.9 vs. 38.6 vs. 40.0% of total FAME for Control, BSF10, BSF15, respectively; p < 0.001). This result was determined by the significant increase of C14:1 n-9, C16:1 n-9, and C18:1 n-11 ( p < 0.001) FA.
